abstract: >
  The Immortality Index is an open-science binary milestone registry that tracks
  progress toward engineered negligible senescence across two parallel research tracks:
  Track 01 (Somatic Genetic Maintenance) and Track 02 (Autonomous Nanorobotic Intervention).
  Each of the 26 research obstacles is defined by a precise theoretical target and
  binary validation-tier milestones. Milestone state is updated nightly by an automated AI
  literature scanner enforcing strict inclusion criteria. The framework provides a
  falsifiable, publicly auditable dependency graph for the global longevity research community.
